[[Beta-carboline]]s are "reversible" MAO-A inhibitors. They are found in some plants used to make [[Ayahuasca]]. In high doses the harmala alkaloids are somewhat hallucinogenic on their own. β-carboline is a [[benzodiazepine receptor]] [[inverse agonist]] and can therefore have convulsive, [[anxiogenic]] and memory enhancing effects.<ref name="pmid17334612">{{cite journal |vauthors=Venault P, Chapouthier G | title = From the behavioral pharmacology of beta-carbolines to seizures, anxiety, and memory | journal = ScientificWorldJournal | volume = 7 | pages = 204–23 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17334612 | pmc = 5901106 | doi = 10.1100/tsw.2007.48 | doi-access = free }}</ref>

